CatDescriptText: Mr. Levy Williams, Westinghouse employee, Fifth Ward and Mr. Chandler Sirmons, Alcoa employee, Homewood, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, February 17, 1962, pg. A3
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Levy Williams wearing dark cap and houndstooth coat, standing in front of building, Downtown; Portrait of Chandler Sirmons wearing cap, eyeglasses, dark bow tie, and dark zippered jacket, standing in front of store, Downtown
